Proverbs 12-8 <t>A man is commended according to his good sense, </t><t>but one of twisted mind is <f>ⓞ</f>despised.</t>
Proverbs 12-9 <t>Better to be lowly and have a servant </t><t>than to play the great man and lack bread.</t>
Proverbs 12-10 <t><f>ⓟ</f> Whoever is righteous has regard for the life of his beast, </t><t>but the mercy of the wicked is cruel.</t>
Proverbs 12-11 <t><f>ⓠ</f> Whoever works his land <f>ⓡ</f>will have plenty of bread, </t><t><f>ⓢ</f>but he who follows <f>ⓣ</f>worthless pursuits lacks sense.</t>
Proverbs 12-12 <t>Whoever is wicked covets <f>ⓤ</f>the spoil of evildoers, </t><t>but the root of the righteous bears fruit.</t>
