Proverbs 12-14 <t>From the fruit of his mouth <f>ⓧ</f>a man is satisfied with good, </t><t><f>ⓨ</f>and the work of a man's hand comes back to him.</t>
Proverbs 12-15 <t><f>ⓩ</f> The way of a fool is right in his own eyes, </t><t>but a wise man listens to advice.</t>
Proverbs 12-16 <t><f>ⓐ</f> The vexation of a fool is known at once, </t><t>but the prudent ignores an insult.</t>
Proverbs 12-17 <t><f>ⓑ</f> Whoever speaks <f>[2]</f> the truth gives honest evidence, </t><t>but <f>ⓒ</f>a false witness utters deceit.</t>
