Proverbs 12-19 <t>Truthful lips endure forever, </t><t>but <f>ⓕ</f>a lying tongue is but for a moment.</t>
Proverbs 12-20 <t>Deceit is in the heart of <f>ⓖ</f>those who devise evil, </t><t>but those who plan peace have joy.</t>
Proverbs 12-21 <t><f>ⓗ</f> No ill befalls the righteous, </t><t>but the wicked are filled with trouble.</t>
Proverbs 12-22 <t><f>ⓘ</f> Lying lips are <f>ⓙ</f>an abomination to the LORD, </t><t><f>ⓚ</f>but those who act faithfully are his delight.</t>
